<item>
            <title>[LU-12804] add llapi interface to FLDB for FID-&gt;target mapping</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12804</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be good to have a user interface for mapping FIDs to MDT/OST targets using the FID Location Database (FLDB).  FLDB is available in memory on all clients, and in the &lt;tt&gt;fld.&amp;#42;.fldb&lt;/tt&gt; file on the MDS. It might make sense to also add a &lt;tt&gt;fld.&amp;#42;.fldb&lt;/tt&gt; file on the clients to facilitate this mapping (good for consistency with MDS, but problematic because it is not a &quot;simple&quot; file and would have to go into &lt;tt&gt;debugfs&lt;/tt&gt; that is root only), or it could be an ioctl (easy to implement, but hard to run on the servers).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
